#### Using the numbered pins on the micro:bit, you can create circuits of your own that include external components, such as LEDs and buttons. The specifics of how a circuit gets wired depends on the specific hardware you're trying to add, but all circuits will use some combinations of a 3 volt power pin (which provide power), a ground pin (which is the end point of a circuit), and numbered data pins (which can either send an output signal, or read an input).

