## Creating LED Circuits

#### One of the simplest circuits that you can make with your micro:bit is to add an LED. To create this circuit you'll need a numbered pin, two wires, an LED, and a ground pin (as well as a level programmed to light up the LED).

#### **1)** Make sure your micro:bit is unplugged from the computer. This helps make sure there isn't any accidental electricity that can damage your board.

#### **2)** Attach a wire so one end is connected to the 0 pad on the micro:bit, and the other end is connected to the positive end of an LED.

#### **3)** Attach a wire so one end is connected to the GND pad on the micro:bit, and the other end is connected to the negative end of an LED.


## LED Debugging

#### LEDs are pretty simple to use, but there are a couple of tricks to keep in mind. You need to pay attention to which direction the electricity is flowing, because LEDs only work in one direction. Always connect the positive side of your LED to your power source and the negative side to ground.
